PSFolderAcl
public class PSObjectAcl
extends PSDbComponentSet

The class represents a collection of ACL entries. Each ACL entries represents a level of access for a particular user, role or virtual entry (Folder Community, Everyone) on a specified securable object such as a "folder". This class acts as a Set even though it does not implement the Set interface. A PSObjectAclEntry object is considered a duplicate if it represents permissions for the same user, role, or virtual entry as another existing object in this collection. Adding a duplicate PSObjectAclEntry returns false from the add() method and the collection does not change. Adding a collection of PSObjectAclEntry objects using addAll() method returns true even if the collection being added contains objects already existing in this collection. However the resulting collection does not contain any duplicate entries.

This class needs to extend PSDbComponentSet to use the functionality of storing state (new, modified, unmodified, markedfordelete) of ACL entries. The state of ACL entries is used while serializing it to the database (in the PSServerFolderProcessor class). Each ACL entry in this collection should be in one of the DBSTATE_xxx state.
